table_caption: List of brain regions of interest (ROIs) that differed significantly between morning and evening sessions (t: time) and between the “lark” and “owl” participants (c: chronotype). P-values were computed using 30,000 permutations followed by Benjamini–Hochberg correction in a two-way ANOVA; FDR was set to 0.05 and the asterisks indicate statistically significant corrected p-values).
